metadata.dc:description: Blind ureter is a rare and incidental condition that, alike other congenital diseases, can be associated to other urological malformations. This papers presents one case report of a blind ureter diagnosed as a result of a apparent anaemic haematuria from the left renoureteral system due to unspecific diffused pyelitis.
metadata.dc:title: Uréter ciego diagnosticado a través de una hematuria.
[Blind ureter diagnosed through hematuria].
